{"title": "Usage of insecure websocket connection", "summary": "  Applications should only connect to APIs using SSL connections. This rule checks that all websocket connections use SSL. ", "description": "\n\nApplications should only connect to APIs using SSL connections. This rule\nchecks that all websocket connections use SSL.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid using unsecured outgoing websocket communication:\n\n```ruby\nclient = Faye::WebSocket::Client.new('ws://insecure-api.com')\n```\n\n\u2705 Always connect using SSL:\n\n```ruby\nclient = Faye::WebSocket::Client.new('wss://secure-api.com')\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-319"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/ruby_lang_websocket_insecure", "https://owasp.org/www-community/vulnerabilities/Insecure_Transport"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}